reviewText: so far so good :) Not to hard on me and I am in my 30th week of pregnancy :)
I love this dvd. The stretches make me feel so relaxed before bed!

I needed something to get me motivated, other than a(n expensive) personal trainer and/or gym membership.  A friend lent this DVD to me, "No you're not pregnant but just try it!"  I'm not pregnant, nor am I a dancer- my hesitation was palpable.  Sections are short and sweet, literally.  Suzanne actually makes working out fun!  And sexy.  The best part- you can modify your workout according to the time you do or don't have!

This is a great video!  It works up slowly from breathing exercises into cardio.  The salsa fusion is really fun, and the workout is challenging enough that I partnered up with my best friend who is not pregnant!  She even touches on Kegel exercises at the end, which is helpful.  If you do not have any dance experience it may take you a while to figure out what she is talking about.  This is a video created for dancers!
